         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">26/8/62 ¶ My dear Professor, ¶  ¶ On the 6. of Aug. I forwarded to Mr. W Pamplin of London pr “Moravian” 2 cases for the Museum and in one of these you will find some dry plants from tropical Australi...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">62.08.26c</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Adolphe Brongniart</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Muséum National d’Histoire Naturelle, Laboratoire de Phanerogamie, Paris.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">The file includes an apparently unrelated description, in M’s hand, of </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Aristolochia praevenosa</seg>
                     <seg style="">.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>26/8/62</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Professor,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On the 6. of Aug. I forwarded to Mr. W Pamplin of London pr “Moravian” 2 cases for the Museum and in one of these you will find some dry plants from tropical Australia. This collection will be completed hereafter. I was fortunate enough to obtain yet 1 copy of the report on Babbages plants<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B59.04.02. </p>
               </note> &amp;send it today to you.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Since you evince much interest on <name key="Rhamneae">Rhamneae</name> I enclose fragments of a new genus recently published in the Fragmenta.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M erected <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Emmenosperma</seg> (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">E. alphitinioides</seg>) in B62.09.01, p. 63.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>From a remark by M Ramel<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found.</p>
               </note> I am informed that you &amp; your excellent colleagues of the Muséum d’histoire naturelle found me worthy of electing me one of the Museum’s correspondent,<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See Muséum d'Histoire Naturelle, Paris to M, 22 July 1862. The diploma would not have reached M by the time this letter was written.</p>
               </note> a honour which I the more highly appreciate as it was so little deserved &amp; which places me under so great obligation to you, that I shall doubly exert myself, to show my gratitude for this distinction.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever with deep</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>veneration</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Mons </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">le Prof Adolphe Brogniart<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">i.e. Brongniart.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">&amp;c <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp;c <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp;c</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
